            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/psyc-436" class="program-course-title">
              PSYC 436 Human Sexuality and Its Problems (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-34423" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Psychology (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Psychology              : This course will deal with typical sexual behavior and its variations. Topics will include the history of sex research, the sexual response cycle, sexual dysfunction, gender identity, sexual orientation, etc. Current research and theory will be emphasized.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

